  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.topSet": "Top set",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.topSet.desc": "Your main heavy set for the day. After warm-up, perform one top set at the heaviest load you can handle for the target rep range with solid technique.\n\ne.g. On bench press, after build-up sets, your heaviest set of 5 reps at 100 kg.",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.backOffSet": "Back-off set",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.backOffSet.desc": "Sets done after the top set, usually 10–20% lighter, to add volume with more controlled fatigue.\n\ne.g. If your top set was 100 kg, next sets at 85 kg for 8–10 reps.",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.clusterSets": "Cluster sets",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.clusterSets.desc": "Split one set into mini-bunches with very short rests (10–30 s) between them so you can handle heavier weight for more total reps than in one straight set.\n\ne.g. Instead of 6 straight squats: 2, rest 15 s, 2, rest 15 s, 2.",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.myoReps": "Myo-reps",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.myoReps.desc": "Maximize fibre recruitment quickly: an initial set near failure, 10–15 s rest, then mini-sets of a few reps at the same weight until you miss the target reps.\n\ne.g. 15 leg extensions, rest 10 s, then 3s until you only get 2.",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.dropSet": "Drop set",
  "coach.routine.advancedTechnique.dropSet.desc": "Push past initial failure: work to failure, immediately reduce load (often 20–30%) and continue for more reps.\n\ne.g. Curl 20 kg to failure, switch to 14 kg and keep repping.",
